Others: Devin Booker returned to the Phoenix Suns after a 5-game absence due to a left groin strain.
Booker had a rusty game shooting from the field, going 4-20, but had a game-high 9 assists.
Coach Mike Budenholzer highlighted Booker's playmaking as a crucial element of the offense.
Booker's playmaking helps open up the floor for other players, especially when Kevin Durant and Bradley Beal are on the court.
Bradley Beal was ruled out of the game due to a left hip contusion.
